INSERT INTO `idm232_recipe_sheet` (`id`, `Title`, `Bio`, `Ingredients`, `Cook_Time`, `Filter`, `Recipe_Img`, `Ingredients_Img`, `Steps_Img`, `Recipe`, `Folder`) VALUES
(2, 'Ancho-Orange Chicken With Kale Rice & Roasted Carrots', 'Weʼre amping up chicken breasts with a glaze of smoky ancho chile paste and fresh\norange juice in this recipe. On the side, roasted carrots and lightly creamy, golden\nraisin-studded rice perfectly accent the sweetness of the glaze.', '4 Boneless, Skinless Chicken Breasts\n1 Tbsp Ancho Chile Paste\n2 Tbsps Crème Fraîche\n3 Tbsps Golden Raisins', '45min', 'Chicken', '0101_FPP_Chicken-Rice_97338_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '0101_ING_FPP_large_feature.png', '0101_FPP_Chicken-Rice_18594_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPP_Chicken-Rice_18622_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPP_Chicken-Rice_18626_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPP_Chicken-Rice_18609_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPP_Chicken-Rice_18639_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPP_Chicken-Rice_18630_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Cook the Rice. Preheat the oven to 450°F and place an oven rack in the center. In a medium pot, combine the rice, a big pinch of salt, and 1½ cups of water. Bring to a boil over high heat. Once boiling, cover and reduce the heat to low. Cook for 12–14 minutes, or until the water has been absorbed and the rice is tender. Turn off the heat, fluff with a fork, and keep covered to stay warm.\n\nPrepare the Ingredients & Make the Glaze: While the rice cooks, wash and dry all fresh produce. Peel the carrots; quarter them lengthwise, then halve crosswise. Peel and roughly chop the garlic. Remove and discard the stems of the kale, then finely chop the leaves. Using a peeler or zester, remove the lime zest (avoiding the white pith) to get about 2 teaspoons. Halve the lime crosswise. Halve the orange and squeeze the juice into a bowl, straining out any seeds. Whisk in the ancho chile paste and 2 tablespoons of water to create the glaze.\n\nRoast the Carrots: Place the sliced carrots on a sheet pan. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat evenly. Arrange the carrots in a single layer and roast for 15–17 minutes, or until tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven and set aside.\n\nCook the Kale & Combine with Rice: While the carrots roast, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add the chopped garlic and cook for 30 seconds to 1 minute, stirring constantly, until fragrant. Add the kale and season with salt and pepper. Cook for 3–4 minutes, or until slightly wilted, then add ⅓ cup of water and continue cooking for another 3–4 minutes, until the kale is tender and the water has evaporated. Transfer the kale to the pot of rice and stir to combine. Season to taste with salt and pepper, then cover to keep warm. Wipe out the pan.\n\nCook & Glaze the Chicken: While the carrots finish roasting, pat the chicken dry with paper towels and season both sides with salt and pepper. In the same pan, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and cook for 4–6 minutes on the first side, until browned. Flip and cook for 2–3 minutes on the other side, until lightly browned. Add the prepared ancho-orange glaze and cook, spooning the glaze over the chicken, for 2–3 minutes, or until the chicken is coated and cooked through. Turn off the heat and stir in the butter and the juice of half a lime until melted. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\nFinish & Serve: To the pot of rice and kale, add the lime zest, crème fraîche, golden raisins, and the juice of the remaining lime half. Stir to combine and season to taste. Serve the glazed chicken with the creamy lime-kale rice and roasted carrots.', 'Recipe_Ancho-Orange_Chicken_with_Kale_Rice_Roasted_Carrots'),
(3, 'Mushroom & Potato Tacos With Romaine & Orange Salad', 'Earthy mushrooms and golden potatoes come together as a comforting, plant-forward taco filling, seasoned and sautéed until tender with a subtle savory depth. Wrapped in warm tortillas and served alongside a crisp romaine and juicy orange salad, this dish pairs hearty textures with refreshing citrus brightness—a simple, satisfying taco night with an unexpected twist.', '4 Flour Tortillas\n3 oz Radishes\n1 Orange\n3⁄4 lb Yukon Gold Potatoes 6 oz Cremini Mushrooms 1 Shallot\n3 Tbsps Roasted Peanuts\n1⁄4 cup Sour Cream\n1 oz Sliced Pickled Jalapeño Pepper\n1 oz Golden Or Red Sweet Piquante Peppers\n1 Tbsp Spanish Spice Blend (Smoked Paprika, Ground Cumin, Ground Coriander, Dried Mexican Oregano, Cayenne Pepper, & Ground Cinnamon)\n1 Romaine Lettuce Heart 2 Tbsps Rice Vinegar', '35min', 'Vegetarian', '1225_2PV2_Mushroom-Potato-Tacos_100074_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_12-25_2PV2_large_feature.png', '1225_2PV2_Chorizo-Tacos_00103_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV2_Mushroom-Potato-Tacos_18402_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV2_Chorizo-Tacos_00125_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV2_Mushroom-Potato-Tacos_18407_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV2_Mushroom-Potato-Tacos_18434_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV2_Mushroom-Potato-Tacos_18424_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Roast the Vegetables: Preheat oven to 450°F. Wash and dry produce. Quarter the mushrooms. Quarter the potatoes lengthwise, then cut crosswise into ½-inch pieces. Place on a sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt, pepper, and ¾ of the spice blend. Toss to coat and roast 21–23 minutes, until browned and tender. Remove from the oven.\n\nPrepare the Remaining Ingredients: Roughly chop the piquante peppers. Peel and small-dice the shallot. Roughly chop the lettuce. Peel and medium-dice the orange. Halve and thinly slice the radishes. Roughly chop the jalapeño. In a bowl, combine sour cream, a drizzle of olive oil, and the remaining spice blend to taste; season with salt and pepper.\n\nWarm the Tortillas: Wrap the tortillas tightly in foil and warm in the oven 5–7 minutes until pliable. Unwrap carefully.\n\nMake the Pepper Relish: In a medium bowl, combine the chopped piquante peppers, diced shallot, half the vinegar, and chopped jalapeño to taste. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n\nMake the Salad: Combine the chopped lettuce, diced orange, sliced radishes, peanuts, and remaining vinegar in a medium bowl. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n\nAssemble the Tacos & Serve: Spread the seasoned sour cream onto the warmed tortillas. Top with the roasted vegetables and pepper relish. Serve with the salad on the side. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Mushroom_Potato_Tacos_with_Romaine_Orange_Salad'),
(4, 'Roasted Chicken & Fall Vegetables With with Cranberry & Ginger Compote', 'For this comforting autumn dinner, weʼre seasoning half chickens with the classic flavors of garlic, onion, and smoked paprika, then roasting them along with sweet potatoes and Brussels sprouts. The rich chicken finds delicious contrast in a tart-sweet compote, made simply by cooking fresh cranberries and ginger with a bit of sugar and water.', '1 lb Sweet Potatoes\n4 oz Cranberries\n1⁄2 lb Brussels Sprouts\n2 Tbsps Apple Cider Vinegar 2 Tbsps Sugar\n1 1-Inch Piece Ginger\n1⁄4 cup Roasted Walnuts\n1 Tbsp Weeknight Hero Spice Blend (Garlic Powder, Onion Powder, Smoked Paprika, & Whole Dried Parsley)', '55min', 'Chicken', '1120_FPP_Roasted-Chicken_92314_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '1120_ING_FPP_large_feature.png', '1120_FPP_Roasted-Chicken_92274_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1120_FPP_Roasted-Chicken_92217_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1120_FPP_Roasted-Chicken_92263_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1120_FPP_Roasted-Chicken_92259_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1120_FPP_Roasted-Chicken_92267_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1120_FPP_Roasted-Chicken_92281_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Roast the Chicken: Preheat oven to 450°F. Line a sheet pan with foil. Pat the chicken dry and season with salt, pepper, and spice blend. Drizzle with olive oil, coat, and arrange skin side up. Roast 36–38 minutes until internal temperature reaches 165°F. Reserve drippings and let chicken rest 5 minutes.\n\nPrepare the Ingredients: Dice the sweet potatoes. Trim and halve the Brussels sprouts.\n\nRoast the Vegetables: Place the sweet potatoes and Brussels sprouts on a sheet pan. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Roast 24–26 minutes, stirring halfway, until lightly browned and tender. Top with vinegar and toss. Keep warm.\n\nPrepare Remaining Ingredients: Peel and finely chop the ginger. Roughly chop the walnuts.\n\nMake the Cranberry Compote: In a small saucepan, combine cranberries, sugar, ginger, and ¼ cup water; season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then cook 4–6 minutes over medium-high until thickened. Transfer to a serving dish.\n\nCarve & Serve: Separate leg from thigh and breast. Slice breast crosswise. Serve chicken with vegetables, top with drippings, and garnish with walnuts. Serve compote on the side. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Roasted_Chicken_Fall_Vegetables_with_Cranberry_Ginger_Compote'),
(5, 'Roasted Cauliflower Salad With Caper Brown Butter & Parmesan Breadcrumbs', 'Seasonal salads donʼt get much more satisfying than this. Weʼre bringing roasted cauliflower and sautéed kale together with cheesy toasted breadcrumbs and a briny caper-studded dressing. Served on top, soft-boiled eggs add extra richness.', '2 Cage-Free Farm Eggs 2 cloves Garlic\n1 head Cauliflower\n1 Lemon\n2 Tbsps Butter\n1 Shallot\n1 Tbsp Capers\n3 Tbsps Panko Breadcrumbs\n1⁄4 cup Grated Parmesan Cheese', '45min', 'Vegetarian', '0101_2PV3_Roasted_Cauliflower-Kale-Salad_97243_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_1-1_2PV3_large_feature.png', '0101_2PV3_Roasted-Cauliflower-Kale-Salad_18444_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV3_Roasted-Cauliflower-Kale-Salad_18401_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV3_Roasted-Cauliflower-Kale-Salad_18444_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV3_Roasted-Cauliflower-Kale-Salad_18459_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV3_Roasted-Cauliflower-Kale-Salad_18467_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV3_Roasted-Cauliflower-Kale-Salad_18473_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Roast the Cauliflower: Preheat oven to 450°F. Boil a small pot of water. Wash and dry the produce. Core the cauliflower and cut into small pieces. Spread on a sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt and pepper. Roast 22–24 minutes until lightly browned and tender. Transfer to a large bowl.\n\nPrepare Remaining Ingredients: Peel and thinly slice the shallot. Peel and roughly chop the garlic. Remove kale stems and roughly chop the leaves. Zest 2 teaspoons of lemon rind and quarter the lemon.\n\nCook & Peel the Eggs: Add the eggs to boiling water and cook exactly 7 minutes. Drain and rinse under cold water. Peel when cool enough to handle.\n\nMake Parmesan Breadcrumbs: Heat 2 teaspoons olive oil in a medium pan over medium-high. Add breadcrumbs and season with salt and pepper. Toast 2–4 minutes until lightly browned. Transfer to a bowl, stir in cheese, and season to taste. Wipe out the pan.\n\nCook the Kale & Shallots: In the same pan, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add shallot and garlic; cook 1–2 minutes until softened. Add kale and ¼ cup water; cook 3–4 minutes until wilted. Stir in lemon zest. Combine with roasted cauliflower and season to taste.\n\nMake Brown Butter & Plate: Melt butter in the same pan and cook 1–2 minutes until browned and fragrant. Stir in capers and juice of 4 lemon wedges; season to taste. Top the cauliflower and kale with the brown butter, parmesan breadcrumbs, and peeled eggs (seasoned with salt and pepper). Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Roasted_Cauliflower_Salad_with_Caper_Brown_Butter_Parmesan_Breadcrumbs'),
(6, 'Pork Chorizo Tacos With Cheesy Roasted Potatoes', 'These tacos get plenty of bold flavor from ground chorizo (a type of spiced pork sausage), cooked into a delightfully saucy filling with cabbage and fresh citrus juices. On the side, weʼre livening up roasted potatoes with garlic and Cotija cheese.', '3⁄4 lb Yukon Gold Potatoes\n10 oz Ground Pork Chorizo\n2 Tbsps Crème Fraîche\n2 Tbsps Grated Cotija Cheese', '30min', 'Pork', '0101_2PRE08_Saucy-Chorizo_Tacos_97328_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '0101_ING_2PRE08_large_feature.png', '0101_2PRE08_Saucy-Chorizo_18548_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PRE08_Saucy-Chorizo_18503_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PRE08_Saucy-Chorizo_18571_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PRE08_Saucy-Chorizo_18580_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PRE08_Saucy-Chorizo_18562_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PRE08_Saucy-Chorizo_18584_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Roast the Potatoes: Preheat oven to 450°F. Wash and dry produce. Halve the potatoes, then cut crosswise into ¼-inch pieces. Place on a sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper, and toss to coat. Roast 22–24 minutes until tender, then transfer to a large bowl.\n\nPrepare Remaining Ingredients: Core and thinly slice the cabbage. Halve the orange and squeeze the juice into a bowl. Trim and halve the radishes; thinly slice. Peel and chop the garlic to a paste. Quarter the lime. Combine crème fraîche with the juice of 1 lime wedge, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt and pepper.\n\nCook the Chorizo & Cabbage: Heat 2 teaspoons olive oil in a medium pan. Add the chorizo; season with salt and pepper. Cook 3–5 minutes, breaking apart until browned. Add cabbage and cook 2–3 minutes until softened. Add orange juice and ½ cup water; cook 6–7 minutes until the cabbage is softened and chorizo is cooked. Stir in juice of 2 lime wedges; season to taste.\n\nWarm Tortillas & Season Radishes: Wrap tortillas in foil and warm 5–7 minutes in the oven. Toss sliced radishes with juice of remaining lime wedge, olive oil, salt, and pepper.\n\nFinish Potatoes: Add cheese and garlic paste to the roasted potatoes; stir to coat. Season to taste.\n\nAssemble Tacos & Serve: Divide the chorizo-cabbage filling, seasoned radishes, and lime crème fraîche among warmed tortillas. Serve with cheesy potatoes on the side. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Pork_Chorizo_Tacos_with_Cheesy_Roasted_Potatoes'),
(7, 'Roasted Broccoli & Fregola Sarda Salad', 'This Middle Eastern-inspired recipe is brimming with varied flavors and textures. Toasty pearls of pasta, roasted vegetables (seasoned with savory, herby zaʼatar), crumbled cheese, and chopped almonds all come together in a smooth, nutty dressing.', '2 Cage-Free Farm Eggs\n1⁄2 cup Fregola Sarda Pasta\n1 clove Garlic\n1 lb Broccoli\n1 Red Onion\n1 bunch Mint\n2 Tbsps Tahini\n1 oz Pecorino Romano Cheese\n1 Tbsp Za\'atar Seasoning (Ground Sumac, Sesame Seeds, Salt, Ground Thyme, Whole Dried Oregano, & Crushed Aleppo Pepper)\n3 Tbsps Roasted Almonds 1 Lemon', '50min', 'Vegetarian', '1218_2PV3_Brocoli-Fregola-Sarde_96640_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_12-18_2PV3_large_feature.png', '1218_2PV3_Broccoli-Fregola-Sarde_18471_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_2PV3_Broccoli-Fregola-Sarde_18467_PRINT_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_2PV3_Broccoli-Fregola-Sarde_18503_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_2PV3_Broccoli-Fregola-Sarde_18528_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_2PV3_Broccoli-Fregola-Sarde_18476_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_2PV3_Broccoli-Fregola-Sarde_18538_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Roast the Vegetables: Preheat oven to 450°F. Boil a medium pot of salted water. Wash and dry produce. Trim broccoli stems and cut into small pieces. Peel and thinly slice the onion. Spread broccoli and onion on a sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt, pepper, and za’atar. Roast 20–22 minutes until browned and tender.\n\nPrepare Remaining Ingredients: Quarter and deseed the lemon. Peel and chop the garlic to a paste. Roughly chop the almonds. Crumble the cheese. Pick the mint leaves.\n\nCook the Pasta: Add pasta to boiling water and cook 14–16 minutes until tender. Drain and return to the pot.\n\nCook & Peel the Eggs: Add eggs to boiling water and cook 9 minutes. Rinse under cold water, peel, slice, and season with salt and pepper.\n\nMake the Dressing: Whisk tahini with the juice of all 4 lemon wedges, 2 tablespoons water, and garlic paste to taste. Slowly whisk in 2 tablespoons olive oil and season.\n\nFinish & Serve: Add roasted vegetables, chopped almonds, cheese, dressing, and olive oil to the pasta; stir to combine. Serve topped with seasoned eggs, a drizzle of olive oil, and mint leaves. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Roasted_Broccoli_Fregola_Sarda_Salad_with_HardBoiled_Eggs_Tahini_Dressing'),
(8, 'Roasted Brussels Sprout & Freekeh Salad with Lemon Yogurt & Barrel-Aged Feta', 'This Mediterranean-inspired grain salad is brimming with varied, vibrant flavors. Nutty freekeh and roasted Brussels sprouts get pops of sweetness from pickled peppers and dates, balanced by briny crumbled Feta. To dollop on top, weʼre serving lemon- seasoned yogurt for extra brightness.', '2⁄3 cup Cracked Freekeh\n1⁄2 cup Sheep\'s Milk Yogurt\n2 Carrots\n2 cloves Garlic\n1 Lemon\n1 bunch Mint\n2 Dried Medjool Dates\n2 Tbsps Pickled Peruvian Peppers 13⁄4 oz Barrel-Aged Feta Cheese\n2 Tbsps Roasted Almonds\n1⁄4 tsp Crushed Red Pepper Flakes 3⁄4 lb Brussels Sprouts', '45min', 'Vegetarian', '1225_2PV3_Broccoli-Freekeh_100110_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_12-25_2PV3_large_feature.png', '1225_2PV3_Broccoli-Freekeh_18503_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV3_Broccoli-Freekah_18447_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV3_Broccoli-Freekeh_18475_PRINT_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV3_Broccoli-Freekah_18435_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV3_Broccoli-Freekeh_18508_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV3_Broccoli-Freekeh_18513_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Roast the Vegetables: Preheat oven to 450°F. Boil a medium pot of salted water and a small pot of water. Wash and dry produce. Trim Brussels sprouts and halve. Peel and cut carrots into 1-inch pieces. Place on a sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper, and roast 14–16 minutes until tender.\n\nCook the Freekeh: Smash 1 garlic clove and add it with the freekeh to the pot of boiling water. Cook 20–22 minutes until tender, then drain and return to the pot.\n\nPrepare Remaining Ingredients: Zest 2 teaspoons of lemon rind; quarter and deseed the lemon. Peel and chop remaining garlic to a paste. Chop almonds and dates. Pick mint leaves.\n\nMake Lemon Yogurt: In a bowl, combine yogurt, lemon zest, juice of 1 lemon wedge, and garlic paste to taste. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n\nFinish Freekeh Salad: Add peppers, almonds, dates, roasted vegetables, the juice of the remaining lemon wedges, half the mint leaves, and red pepper flakes to the freekeh. Drizzle with olive oil and season.\n\nServe: Serve the freekeh salad with lemon yogurt on the side. Garnish with cheese, remaining mint leaves, and olive oil. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Roasted_Brussels_Sprout_Freekeh_Salad_with_Lemon_Yogurt_Barrel-Aged_Feta'),
(9, 'Smoked Gouda & Mushroom Flatbread With Endive & Apple Salad', 'Stands up to utensils (yes, even metal!), and best of all, itʼs easy to clean.', '1 Endive\n2 cloves Garlic\n2 oz Smoked Gouda Cheese\n2 oz Fontina Or Aged Alpine Cheese\n1 Red Onion\n¾ lb Pizza Dough\n4 oz Cremini Mushrooms\n1 Apple\n1 Tbsp Honey\n1 Tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar', '40min', 'Vegetarian', '0101_2PV2_Smoky-Kale-Flatbread_97386_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_1-1_2PV2_large_feature.png', '0101_2PV2_Smoky-Kale-Mushroom-Flatberad_3151_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV2_Smoky-Kale-Mushroom-Flatberad_3181_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV2_Smoky-Kale-Mushroom-Flatberad_3189_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV2_Smoky-Kale-Mushroom-Flatberad_3207_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV2_Smoky-Kale-Mushroom-Flatberad_3219_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV2_Smoky-Kale-Mushroom-Flatberad_3233_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare the Ingredients: Remove the dough and honey from the refrigerator to bring to room temperature. Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then preheat to 475°F. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Thinly slice the mushrooms. Peel and roughly chop the garlic. Peel and thinly slice the onion. Remove and discard the stems of the kale; roughly chop the leaves. Grate both cheeses on the large side of a box grater (discard any rind) and combine in a bowl.\n\nStart the Vegetables: In a large pan (nonstick if you have one), heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high until hot. Add the sliced mushrooms in an even layer. Cook without stirring 2–3 minutes, or until lightly browned. Add the chopped garlic and sliced onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 2–3 minutes, or until lightly browned and fragrant.\n\nFinish the Vegetables: Add the chopped kale to the pan; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, 1–2 minutes, or until slightly wilted. Add ¼ cup of water; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3–4 minutes, or until the kale has wilted and the water has cooked off. Turn off the heat and season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\nAssemble & Bake the Flatbread: Lightly oil a sheet pan. On a work surface, using your hands and a rolling pin (or wine bottle), gently stretch and roll the dough to a 1/8-inch thickness. If resistant, let rest 5 minutes. Carefully transfer to the sheet pan, rubbing the dough into the pan to coat the bottom with oil. Leaving a 1-inch border, evenly top the dough with the finished vegetables, grated cheeses, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Bake 14–16 minutes, rotating halfway through, until the crust is browned and the cheese has melted. Remove from the oven and let stand at least 2 minutes.\n\nPrepare the Remaining Ingredients: While the flatbread bakes, cut off and discard the root end of the endive; roughly chop the leaves. Core, quarter, and thinly slice the apple. To make the dressing, in a large bowl, whisk together the vinegar, honey (kneading the packet before opening), and 1 tablespoon olive oil until combined. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\nMake the Salad & Serve: Just before serving, add the chopped endive and sliced apple to the dressing. Toss to combine; season with salt and pepper. Serve the baked flatbread with the salad on the side. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Smoked_Gouda_Mushroom_Flatbread_with_Endive_Apple_Salad'),
(10, 'Broccoli & Mozzarella Calzones With Caesar Salad', 'These calzones are loaded with melty fresh mozzarella, creamy ricotta, and tender\nbroccoli—balanced by a tangy tomato dipping sauce. For a refreshing side, weʼre\ntossing crunchy romaine and briny black olives in our take on Caesar dressing.', '1½ lbs Pizza Dough\n3 cloves Garlic\n1 Romaine Lettuce Heart\n1 lb Broccoli\n1 cup Part-Skim Ricotta Cheese\n1 8-Ounce Can Tomato Sauce\n½ lb Fresh Mozzarella Cheese\n¼ cup Grated Parmesan Cheese\n2 oz Black Cerignola Olives\n1 Tbsp Italian Seasoning (Whole Dried Basil, Sage,\nOregano, Savory, Rosemary, Thyme, & Marjoram)\n1 Lemon', '45min', 'Vegetarian', '0101_FPV_Broccoli-Calzones_97286_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '0101_ING_FPV_large_feature.png', '0101_FPV_Broccoli-Mozzarella-Calzones_18498_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPV_Broccoli-Mozzarella-Calzones_18498_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPV_Broccoli-Mozzarella-Calzones_18402_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPV_Broccoli-Mozzarella-Calzones_18410_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPV_Broccoli-Mozzarella-Calzones_18532_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare the Ingredients: Remove the dough from the refrigerator to bring to room temperature. Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then preheat to 475°F. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut off and discard the bottom ½ inch of the broccoli stem, then roughly chop the broccoli. Peel and roughly chop the garlic. Tear the mozzarella cheese into small pieces. Quarter and deseed the lemon.\n\nCook the Broccoli & Make the Filling: In a large pan (nonstick, if available), heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil over medium-high heat until hot. Add the chopped broccoli and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 4–6 minutes, or until lightly browned. Add 2/3 of the chopped garlic and cook, stirring constantly, 30 seconds to 1 minute, until fragrant. Add ¼ cup of water; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 2–3 minutes, until the broccoli has softened and the water has cooked off. Transfer to a large bowl. Add the mozzarella cheese, ricotta cheese, half of the Italian seasoning, and the juice of 1 lemon wedge. Stir to combine and season with salt and pepper. Wipe out the pan.\n\nAssemble & Bake the Calzones: Lightly oil a sheet pan. Divide the dough into 2 equal portions. Using your hands and a rolling pin (or a wine bottle), gently stretch and roll the portions into ¼-inch-thick rounds. (If the dough is resistant, let rest for 5 minutes.) Divide the filling between the centers of the rounds, then fold each round in half over the filling. Use a fork to crimp the edges to seal. Transfer to the sheet pan. Poke a few holes across the tops of the calzones to vent, then lightly drizzle with olive oil. Bake for 16–18 minutes, or until golden brown. Transfer to a cutting board and let stand for at least 2 minutes.\n\nPrepare the Remaining Ingredients: While the calzones bake, smash the olives using the flat side of your knife; remove and discard the pits, then roughly chop. Cut off and discard the root end of the lettuce, then roughly chop the leaves. To make the dressing, in a large bowl, combine the mayonnaise, half of the parmesan cheese, the juice of the remaining lemon wedges, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\nMake the Salad & Serve Your Dish: Just before serving, add the chopped olives and lettuce to the bowl of dressing. Toss to coat and season with salt and pepper to taste. Cut the baked calzones in half. Serve with the tomato sauce and salad on the side, and garnish with the remaining parmesan cheese. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Broccoli_Mozzarella_Calzones_with_Caesar_Salad'),
(11, 'Roasted Turkey Breast & Farro- Endive Salad With Brown Butter Apple Compote', 'Fall comfort food gets a delicious lift in this recipe. A sweet, toasty compote (simply apple and shallot cooked in brown butter) balances our savory roasted turkey breast. On the side, weʼre tossing warm grains with endive—first cooked with a bit of honey and lemon to brighten its mildly bitter flavor.', '1 Turkey Breast Roast\n2⁄3 cup Semi-Pearled Farro\n1 Apple\n1 Lemon\n1 Endive\n1 bunch Chives\n2 Tbsps Butter\n1 Shallot\n1 Tbsp Honey\n1 Tbsp Whole Grain Dijon Mustard', '35min', 'Turkey', '1211_2PRE08_Turkey_98057_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '1211_ING_2PRE08_large_feature.png', '1211_2PRE08_Turkey-Farro_96241_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1211_2PRE08_Turkey-Farro_96205_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1211_2PRE08_Turkey_98039_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1211_2PRE08_Turkey-Farro_96220_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1211_2PRE08_Turkey-Farro_96223_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1211_2PRE08_Turkey-Farro_96234_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Sear & Roast the Turkey: Remove honey from the refrigerator to bring to room temperature. Preheat oven to 450°F. Heat a medium pot of salted water to boiling. Line a sheet pan with foil. Remove netting from the turkey and season with salt and pepper. In a large pan, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium-high. Add turkey skin side down and cook 4–6 minutes until lightly browned. Flip and cook 3–5 minutes. Transfer to the sheet pan, skin side up, leaving fond in the pan. Roast 15–17 minutes until internal temperature reaches 165°F. Let rest at least 5 minutes.\n\nCook the Farro: Add farro to the boiling water and cook 17–19 minutes until tender. Drain and return to the pot; keep warm.\n\nPrepare the Ingredients: Wash and dry produce. Peel and finely chop the shallot. Thinly slice the endive crosswise, discarding the root. Quarter and deseed the lemon. Core and small-dice the apple. Cut chives into ½-inch pieces.\n\nCook the Endive Compote: In the same pan of reserved fond, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium-high. Add half the shallot and cook 30 seconds to 1 minute. Add the endive, season with salt and pepper, and cook 1–2 minutes until softened. Add half the honey and juice of 2 lemon wedges. Cook 30 seconds to 1 minute until combined; transfer to a bowl.\n\nCook the Apple Compote: In the same pan, melt butter over medium-high until browned and fragrant. Add the diced apple and remaining shallot; season with salt and pepper. Cook 1–2 minutes until slightly softened. Add remaining honey and juice of remaining lemon wedges. Cook 30 seconds to 1 minute until combined; remove from heat.\n\nMake the Farro Salad & Serve: Add cooked endive, mustard, half the chives, and a drizzle of olive oil to the farro. Slice the rested turkey. Serve with farro salad and top turkey with apple compote. Garnish with remaining chives and olive oil. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Roasted_Turkey_Breast_FarroEndive_Salad_with_Brown_Butter_Apple_Compote'),
(12, 'Seared Steaks & Garlic Butter With Oven Fries', '“Steak frites,” or steak with french fries, is classic French bistro fare. Tonightʼs steaks get another layer of rich flavor from garlic butter, spooned over them as they cook. Creamy mustard sauce is a perfect match for the rich steaks and hearty oven-roasted fries, while a simple salad adds refreshing contrast. (You may receive crisp romaine or tender butter lettuce.)', '2 cloves Garlic\n2 Russet Potatoes\n1 bunch Chives\n3 Tbsps Creamy Mustard Sauce\n2 Tbsps Butter\n1 Tbsp Red Wine Vinegar', '35min', 'Beef', '1127_FPM_Steak-Fries_94016_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '1127_ING_FPM_large_feature.png', '1127_FPM_Steak-Fries_93957_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_FPM_Steak-Frites_18431_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_FPM_Steak-Frites_18434_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_FPM_Steak-Fries_93961_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_FPM_Steak-Frites_18438_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_FPM_Steak-Fries_93984_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Roast the Potatoes: Preheat oven to 450°F. Wash and dry produce. Cut potatoes into ½-inch sticks. Spread on a sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper, toss, and roast 22–24 minutes, flipping halfway.\n\nPrepare the Remaining Ingredients: Peel and finely chop the garlic. Trim and chop the lettuce. Thinly slice the chives.\n\nMake the Vinaigrette: In a bowl, combine vinegar and ¼ of the creamy mustard sauce. Slowly whisk in 2 teaspoons olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n\nCook the Steaks & Make Garlic Butter: Pat the steaks dry; season with salt and pepper. Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large pan over medium-high. Add steaks and cook 4–5 minutes on the first side and 2–3 minutes on the second side. Add chopped garlic and butter and spoon over steaks 1–2 minutes for medium-rare. Transfer steaks to a cutting board to rest; reserve garlic butter.\n\nPrepare the Salad: Add the chopped lettuce to a bowl, toss with vinaigrette, and season with salt and pepper.\n\nSlice Steaks & Serve: Slice steaks against the grain. Serve with roasted potatoes and salad. Drizzle steaks and potatoes with garlic butter. Garnish salad with chives and serve remaining mustard sauce on the side. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Seared_Steaks_Garlic_Butter_with_Oven_Fries'),
(13, 'Salmon & Honey-Glazed Carrots With Lemon-Saffron Yogurt Sauce', 'This elegant dish gets unique flavor from a prized spice, saffron, used two ways: added to the water used to boil the potatoes and stirred into a creamy yogurt sauce. The bright sauce is delicious spooned over rich salmon, potatoes, and carrots—which get another flavor-packed lift from a glaze of honey and fragrant cumin. Aleppo pepper adds just a hint of spice throughout the dish, balanced by cooling fresh mint.', '2 Skin-On Salmon Fillets \n2 cloves Garlic\n6 oz Carrots\n1 Lemon\n3⁄4 lb Yukon Gold Potatoes\n1 Pinch Saffron\n1 Tbsp Honey\n1⁄2 cup Plain Greek Yogurt\n1⁄2 tsp Crushed Aleppo Pepper \n1⁄2 tsp Ground Cumin', '35min', 'Fish', '1106_2PF_Salmon-Honey-Carrots_94837_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_11-06_2PF_large_feature.png', '1106_2PF_Salmon_90184_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1106_2PF_Salmon-Honey-Carrots_94815_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1106_2PF_Salmon-Honey-Carrots_94819_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1106_2PF_Salmon_90194_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1106_2PF_Salmon_90232_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1106_2PF_Salmon-Honey-Carrots_94819_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Cook the Potatoes: Bring honey to room temperature. Wash and dry produce. Medium dice the potatoes. Place in a small pot with half the saffron and a big pinch of salt. Add water to cover by ½ inch and boil 10–12 minutes until tender. Drain and return to the pot.\n\nPrepare the Remaining Ingredients: Peel carrots and cut into ½-inch angled pieces. Peel and roughly chop the garlic. Pick the mint leaves. Remove lemon rind and finely mince to get 2 teaspoons zest. Quarter and deseed the lemon. In a medium bowl, combine remaining saffron with the juice of 1 lemon wedge.\n\nCook & Glaze the Carrots: In a medium pan, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium-high. Add carrots and garlic; season with salt and pepper. Cook 2–3 minutes, then add cumin and honey. Cook 30 seconds to 1 minute until fragrant. Add ¾ cup water and cook 8–10 minutes until carrots are glazed. Transfer to a bowl.\n\nMake the Yogurt Sauce: Add yogurt, lemon zest, olive oil, and up to half the Aleppo pepper to the saffron-lemon mixture. Season with salt and pepper.\n\nCook the Salmon: Pat salmon dry and season with salt and pepper. In the same pan, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil over medium-high. Add salmon skinless side down and cook 3–4 minutes. Flip and cook 2–3 minutes until done.\n\nFinish & Plate: Add glazed carrots, juice of the remaining lemon wedges, half the mint, and remaining Aleppo pepper to the potatoes; drizzle with olive oil and stir. Serve potatoes topped with salmon and yogurt sauce; garnish with remaining mint. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Salmon_HoneyGlazed_Carrots_with_LemonSaffron_Yogurt_Sauce'),
(14, 'Bucatini Alfredo With Broccoli', 'This quick-cooking recipe captures all the deliciously creamy, rich flavor of the classic\nItalian-American sauce—with the welcome addition of quick-braised broccoli. A dusting\nof pecorino cheese completes each bowl with a touch of sharpness.', '2 Tbsps Crème Fraîche\n¼ tsp Crushed Red Pepper Flakes\n3 Tbsps All-Purpose Flour\n¼ cup Grated Pecorino Cheese', '50min', 'Pasta', '0101_2PV1_Broccoli-Bucatini-Fettuccine_97230_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_1-1_2PV1_large_feature.png', '0101_2PV1_Broccoli-Bucatini-Fettucine_18429_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV1_Broccoli-Bucatini-Fettucine_18403_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV1_Broccoli-Bucatini-Fettucine_18406_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV1_Broccoli-Bucatini-Fettucine_18416_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PV1_Broccoli-Bucatini-Fettucine_18431_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare the Ingredients: Heat a large pot of salted water to boiling over high heat. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut off and discard the bottom ½ inch of the broccoli stem, then cut the broccoli into small pieces, keeping the florets intact. Peel and finely chop the garlic.\n\nCook the Broccoli: In a large pan, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil over medium-high heat until hot. Add the broccoli pieces and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 4–5 minutes, or until slightly softened. Add ½ cup of water; season with salt and pepper. Cover the pan with aluminum foil and cook 3–4 minutes, or until the broccoli has softened and the water has cooked off. Transfer to a bowl and wipe out the pan.\n\nCook the Pasta: While the broccoli cooks, add the pasta to the pot of boiling water and cook 8–10 minutes, or until al dente (still slightly firm to the bite). Reserve ½ cup of the pasta cooking water, then drain thoroughly.\n\nMake the Sauce: In the same pan, heat 1½ tablespoons of olive oil over medium-high heat until hot. Add the chopped garlic and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until fragrant. Add the flour and as much of the red pepper flakes as desired for spiciness. Cook, stirring constantly, 30 seconds to 1 minute, until thoroughly combined. Add the heavy cream (shake the bottle before opening), verjus, and 1¼ cups of water; season with salt and pepper. Cook, whisking frequently, 2–3 minutes, or until thickened. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\nFinish & Serve: Add the cooked pasta, cooked broccoli, crème fraîche, and half of the reserved pasta cooking water to the pan. Cook, stirring vigorously, 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until the pasta is thoroughly coated. If the sauce seems dry, gradually add the remaining reserved pasta cooking water to reach your desired consistency. Turn off the heat and season with salt and pepper to taste. Garnish with the cheese and a sprinkle of pepper. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Bucatini_Alfredo_with_Broccoli'),
(15, 'Spicy Chicken Quesadillas With Beet & Orange Salad', 'A seasonal salad of striped Chioggia beet, juicy orange, and peanuts is a fresh pairing\nfor these zesty quesadillas. Weʼre seasoning the chicken filling with both jalapeño\npepper and Mexican spices—balanced by a layer of melty white cheddar. Mexican\ncrema brightened up with lime juice is perfect for dipping.', '4 Flour Tortillas\n2 Scallions\n6 oz Chioggia Beet\n1 Jalapeño Pepper\n1 Lime\n1 Navel Orange\n3 Tbsps Roasted Peanuts\n2 oz White Cheddar Cheese\n¼ cup Mexican Crema\n1 Tbsp Mexican Spice Blend (Ancho Chile Powder,\nSmoked Paprika, Garlic Powder, Ground Cumin, &\nDried Mexican Oregano)', '20min', 'Chicken', '1127_2PP_Spicy-Chicken-Quesadillas_93502_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_11-27_2PP_large_feature.png', '1127_2PP_Spicy-Chicken-Quesadillas_94039_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_2PP_Spicy-Chicken-Quesadillas_93434_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_2PP_Spicy-Chicken-Quesadillas_93442_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_2PP_Spicy-Chicken-Quesadillas_93449_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_2PP_Spicy-Chicken-Quesadillas_93455_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_2PP_Spicy-Chicken-Quesadillas_94045_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Cook the Beet: Heat a small pot of salted water to boiling on high. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Peel the beet and cut lengthwise into ¼-inch wedges. Once the water is boiling, add the beet wedges and cook uncovered 22–24 minutes, or until tender when pierced with a fork. Drain and rinse under cold water for 30 seconds to 1 minute to stop cooking. Pat dry and transfer to a large bowl.\n\nPrepare the Remaining Ingredients: While the beet cooks, cut off and discard the root ends of the scallions; thinly slice, separating the white bottoms and green tops. Using a peeler, remove the green rind of the lime, avoiding the white pith; mince to get 2 teaspoons zest. Quarter the lime. Grate the cheese on the large side of a box grater. Peel the orange; halve lengthwise, then thinly slice crosswise. To make the lime crema, in a bowl, combine the crema and juice of 2 lime wedges; season with salt and pepper. Cut out and discard the stem, ribs, and seeds of the pepper; finely chop. Wash hands, knife, and cutting board after handling.\n\nCook & Chop the Chicken: Pat the chicken dry with paper towels; season both sides with salt, pepper, and spice blend. In a large pan (nonstick if available), heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium-high until hot. Add the seasoned chicken; cook 3–4 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through. Transfer to a cutting board; when cool, roughly chop and transfer to a medium bowl. Rinse and wipe out the pan.\n\nMake the Filling & Assemble the Quesadillas: To the bowl of chopped chicken, add the sliced white scallion bottoms, lime zest, juice of 1 lime wedge, a drizzle of olive oil, and chopped pepper to taste. Stir to combine; season with salt and pepper. Place the tortillas on a work surface. Sprinkle grated cheese on one side of each tortilla. Evenly top with filling and fold in half.\n\nCook the Quesadillas: In the same pan, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium until hot. Add the quesadillas; cook 2–3 minutes per side, or until tortillas are browned and cheese has melted. If the pan is dry, add a drizzle of olive oil before flipping. Transfer to a cutting board and immediately season with salt and pepper.\n\nMake the Salad & Serve: While the quesadillas cook, add sliced orange, peanuts, juice of the remaining lime wedge, and a drizzle of olive oil to the bowl of cooked beet. Stir to combine; season with salt and pepper. Cut the cooked quesadillas in half. Garnish the quesadillas and salad with sliced green scallion tops. Serve with lime crema on the side. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Spicy_Chicken_Quesadillas_with_Beet_Orange_Salad'),
(16, 'Cheesy Enchiladas Rojas With Mushrooms & Kale', 'Our hearty vegetarian enchiladas are filled with a combination of fragrant, Mexicanspiced\nrice and sautéed mushrooms and kale. For even more flavor, weʼre baking them\nunder a smoky-sweet tomato sauce flavored with ancho chile paste and a layer of melty\nwhite cheddar. A dollop of lime-seasoned sour cream adds creamy, cooling balance.\n(You may receive green curly, dark green lacinato, or red kale.)', '8 Flour Tortillas\n¾ cup Jasmine Rice\n1 28-Ounce Can Whole Peeled Tomatoes\n4 oz Cremini Mushrooms\n3 cloves Garlic\n1 Yellow Onion\n1 bunch Chives\n2 Tbsps Ancho Chile Paste\n1 Tbsp Mexican Spice Blend (Ancho Chile Powder,\nSweet Paprika, Garlic Powder, Ground Cumin, &\nWhole Mexican Oregano)\n½ lb White Cheddar Cheese\n½ cup Sour Cream', '25min', 'Vegetarian', '1120_FPV_Emchiladas_74891_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '1218_FPV_Enchiladas_18459_WEB_high_feature.jpg', '1218_FPV_Enchiladas_18473_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_FPV_Enchiladas_18459_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_FPV_Enchiladas_18492_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_FPV_Enchiladas_18507_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_FPV_Enchiladas_18515_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare the Rice & Preheat the Oven: Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then preheat to 450°F. In a medium pot, combine the rice, half the spice blend, a big pinch of salt, and 1½ cups of water. Heat to boiling over high heat. Once boiling, cover and reduce the heat to low. Cook 12–14 minutes, or until the water has been absorbed and the rice is tender. Turn off the heat, fluff with a fork, and transfer to a large bowl. Keep warm.\n\nPrepare the Ingredients & Make the Lime Sour Cream: While the rice cooks, wash and dry the fresh produce. Thinly slice the mushrooms. Remove and discard the stems of the kale, then roughly chop the leaves. Peel and roughly chop the garlic. Peel and thinly slice the onion. Place the tomatoes in a bowl and gently break apart with your hands. Grate the cheese on the large side of a box grater. Thinly slice the chives. Halve the lime. In a bowl, combine the sour cream, juice of 1 lime half, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\nCook the Vegetables & Start the Filling: In a large pan, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil over medium-high heat until hot. Add the sliced mushrooms in an even layer. Cook without stirring 2–3 minutes, or until lightly browned. Add the chopped kale and ½ cup of water; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, 4–5 minutes, or until the kale has wilted and the water has cooked off. Transfer to the bowl of cooked rice and stir to combine. Wipe out the pan.\n\nFinish the Filling & Assemble the Enchiladas: Add half the cheese and the juice of the remaining lime half to the bowl of filling. Stir to combine and season with salt and pepper to taste. Place the tortillas on a work surface. Spread about half the sauce into the bottom of a baking dish. Divide the filling among the tortillas, tightly rolling each around the filling. Transfer to the baking dish, seam side down. Evenly top with the remaining sauce and remaining cheese.\n\nBake the Enchiladas & Serve: Bake 10–12 minutes, or until the cheese has melted. Remove from the oven and let stand for at least 2 minutes. Garnish with the sliced chives. Serve with the lime sour cream. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Cheesy_Enchiladas_Rojas_with_Mushrooms_Kale'),
(17, 'Roasted Red Pepper Pasta With Lemon-Parmesan Broccoli', 'In this quick-cooking recipe, whole grain pipe rigate gets pops of flavor from sweet roasted piquillo peppers and briny capers—plus a layer of exciting crunch from almonds. It all comes together in a creamy, mildly spicy sauce.', '6 oz Whole Grain Pipe Rigate Pasta 2 oz Roasted Piquillo Peppers\n2 Tbsps Grated Parmesan Cheese 2 Tbsps Sliced Roasted Almonds 11⁄2 tsps Calabrian Chile Paste', '30min', 'Pasta', '0108_2PV1_Roasted-Pepper-Pasta_97907_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_1-8_2PV1_large_feature.png', '0108_2PV1_Roasted-Pepper-Pasta_97872_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PV1_Roasted-Pepper-Pasta_97867_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PV1_Roasted-Pepper-Pasta_97877_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PV1_Roasted-Pepper-Pasta_97881_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PV1_Roasted-Pepper-Pasta_97889_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Roast the Broccoli: Preheat oven to 450°F. Heat a large pot of salted water to boiling. Wash and dry the broccoli. Trim the bottom ½ inch of the stems and cut into small pieces. Quarter and deseed the lemon. Spread broccoli on a sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper, and roast 16–18 minutes. Top with juice of 2 lemon wedges.\n\nCook the Pasta: Add pasta to boiling water and cook 8–10 minutes until al dente. Reserve ½ cup pasta water and drain.\n\nPrepare Remaining Ingredients: Peel and roughly chop the garlic. Finely chop the peppers.\n\nMake the Sauce: Heat 2 teaspoons olive oil in a pan over medium-high. Add capers, garlic, and peppers; season with salt and pepper. Cook 2–3 minutes until lightly browned. Add tomato paste and chile paste if desired. Cook 1–2 minutes. Turn off heat and stir in heavy cream and ¼ cup water; season to taste.\n\nFinish Pasta & Serve: Add the pasta, butter, and half the reserved pasta water to the sauce. Cook 30 seconds to 1 minute, adding more water as needed. Serve with roasted broccoli and remaining lemon wedges. Garnish pasta with almonds and half the cheese; garnish broccoli with remaining cheese. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Roasted_Red_Pepper_Pasta_with_LemonParmesan_Broccoli'),
(18, 'Spicy Pork & Korean Rice Cakes With Bok Choy', 'In this crowd-pleasing recipe, a savory and spicy sauce (balanced by a touch of cooling\ncrème fraîche) brings together ground pork, bok choy, and aromatics. Weʼre mixing in\ndelightfully chewy tteok, or rice cakes—a staple of Korean cuisine.', '1 lb Korean Rice Cakes\n2 cloves Garlic\n2 heads Baby Bok Choy\n2 Tbsps Soy Glaze\n1½ Tbsps Gochujang\n1 1-Inch Piece Ginger\n¼ cup Black Bean Sauce\n¼ cup Crème Fraîche\n1 bunch Chives', '30min', 'Pork', '1225_FPM_Rice-Cakes_100092_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '1225_ING_FPM_large_feature.png', '1225_FPM_Rice-Cakes_18459_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_FPM_Pork-Rice-Cakes_18453_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_FPM_Pork-Rice-Cakes_18446_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_FPM_Pork-Rice-Cakes_00082_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_FPM_Pork-Rice-Cakes_00096_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare the Ingredients: Heat a large pot of salted water to boiling on high. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Peel and finely chop the ginger. Peel and roughly chop the garlic. Cut off and discard the root end of the bok choy; roughly chop the leaves and stems, keeping them separate. Thinly slice the chives.\n\nCook the Pork: In a large pan, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium until hot. Add the ground pork and season with salt and pepper. Cook 4–6 minutes, frequently breaking the meat apart, until lightly browned. Add the chopped ginger and garlic; season with salt and pepper. Cook 2–3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until softened and pork is cooked through.\n\nCook the Bok Choy Stems: Add the chopped bok choy stems, soy glaze, black bean sauce, ½ cup water, and gochujang to taste. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3–4 minutes, until stems are softened and liquid is thickened. Turn off the heat and season with salt and pepper.\n\nCook the Rice Cakes: While the sauce cooks, add the rice cakes to the pot of boiling water and cook 2–3 minutes, or until tender. Drain thoroughly.\n\nFinish & Serve: Add the cooked rice cakes and chopped bok choy leaves to the pan of pork and sauce. Cook 1–2 minutes over medium-high, stirring frequently, until the rice cakes are coated and the leaves are slightly wilted. Turn off the heat and stir in half the sliced chives. Garnish with remaining chives and pepper. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Spicy_Pork_Korean_Rice_Cakes_with_Bok_Choy');
INSERT INTO `idm232_recipe_sheet` (`id`, `Title`, `Bio`, `Ingredients`, `Cook_Time`, `Filter`, `Recipe_Img`, `Ingredients_Img`, `Steps_Img`, `Recipe`, `Folder`) VALUES
(19, 'Seared Chicken & Mashed Potatoes With Maple-Glazed Carrots', 'Weʼre giving seared chicken a lift with a rich pan sauce, made with sweet maple syrup and tangy sherry vinegar. Itʼs the perfect accompaniment for creamy mashed potatoes and roasted carrots, dressed with a bit more maple syrup.', '2 Boneless, Skinless Chicken Breasts 3⁄4 lb Yukon Gold Potatoes\n2 Tbsps Crème Fraîche\n1 Tbsp Sherry Vinegar', '55min', 'Chicken', '0108_2PP_Chicken-Mashed-Potatoes_98562_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_1-8_2PP_large_feature.png', '0108_2PP_Chicken-Mashed-Potatoes_98479_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PP_Chicken-Mashed-Potatoes_98533_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PP_Chicken-Mashed-Potatoes_98516_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PP_Chicken-Mashed-Potatoes_98538_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PP_Chicken-Mashed-Potatoes_98552_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PP_Chicken-Mashed-Potatoes_98546_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare Ingredients: Place oven rack in center and preheat to 450°F. Heat a medium pot of salted water to boiling. Wash and dry produce. Peel carrots; quarter lengthwise and halve crosswise. Large-dice the potatoes.\n\nRoast & Glaze Carrots: Spread carrots on a sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper, and roast 15–17 minutes until lightly browned and tender. Transfer to a bowl, add half the maple syrup, and toss. Loosely cover to keep warm.\n\nCook & Mash Potatoes: Add potatoes to boiling water and cook 14–16 minutes until tender. Drain and return to the pot. Add crème fraîche and 1 tablespoon olive oil; mash to desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper; cover to keep warm.\n\nCook Chicken: Pat chicken dry; season with salt and pepper. Heat 2 teaspoons olive oil in a medium pan over medium-high. Add chicken and cook 5–7 minutes per side until cooked through. Transfer to a cutting board, leaving fond in the pan.\n\nMake Pan Sauce: Add vinegar and remaining maple syrup to the pan; cook 30 seconds to 1 minute, stirring and scraping up fond. Stir in butter and season with salt and pepper.\n\nSlice Chicken & Serve: Slice chicken crosswise. Serve with mashed potatoes and glazed carrots, and spoon pan sauce over top. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Seared_Chicken_Mashed_Potatoes_with_MapleGlazed_Carrots'),
(20, 'Sweet & Sour Vegetable Stir-Fry With Fried Eggs & Peanuts', 'Two kinds of citrus—seasonal orange and lemon—give the sauce for our stir-fried\nvegetables its irresistible sweet-sour balance. The carrots, celery, and bok choy\nperfectly contrast a rich fried egg and fluffy, radish-studded white rice.', '2 Cage-Free Farm Eggs\n1 1-Inch Piece Ginger\n1½ Tbsps Soy Marinade\n2 Tbsps Roasted Peanuts', '45min', 'Vegetarian', '0108_2PV2_Stir-Fry-Egg_0195_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_1-8_2PV2_large_feature.png', '0108_2PV2_Stir-Fry-Egg_0175_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PV2_Sweet-Sour-Stir-Fry_97727_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PV2_Sweet-Sour-Stir-Fry_97749_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PV2_Sweet-Sour-Stir-Fry_97760_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PV2_Sweet-Sour-Stir-Fry_97772_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n828_2PV2_Lentil-Bowl_81961_PRINT_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare the Ingredients & Marinate the Radish: Wash and dry the fresh produce. Peel the carrots and thinly slice on an angle. Slice the celery on an angle into ½-inch pieces. Halve the orange and squeeze the juice into a medium bowl, straining out the seeds. Peel and roughly chop the garlic. Peel and finely chop the ginger. Cut off and discard the root end of the bok choy; roughly chop. Quarter and deseed the lemon. Small-dice the radishes and place in a bowl with the juice of 1 lemon wedge and half the sesame oil; season with salt and pepper. Marinate at least 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n\nCook the Rice: In a medium pot, combine the rice, a big pinch of salt, and 1½ cups water. Heat to boiling on high. Once boiling, cover and reduce heat to low. Cook 12–14 minutes, or until the water is absorbed and rice is tender. Turn off heat, fluff with a fork, and keep covered.\n\nStart the Stir-Fry: In a large pan, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium-high until hot. Add the sliced carrots and celery; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 6–7 minutes, or until slightly softened.\n\nPrepare the Sauce: To the bowl of orange juice, add soy glaze, soy marinade, and the juice of the remaining lemon wedges. Stir to combine; season with salt and pepper.\n\nFinish the Stir-Fry: Add the chopped garlic, chopped ginger, and remaining sesame oil to the pan of vegetables. Cook 30 seconds to 1 minute, stirring constantly, until fragrant. Add the sauce and chopped bok choy; cook 1–2 minutes, until the bok choy leaves have wilted. Transfer to a bowl and season with salt and pepper.\n\nFry the Eggs & Serve: In the same pan, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium-high until hot. Crack the eggs into the pan; season with salt and pepper. Cook 4–5 minutes, or until whites are set. Stir the marinated radishes (with liquid) into the cooked rice. Serve rice topped with stir-fry, fried eggs, and peanuts. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Sweet_Sour_Vegetable_StirFry_with_Fried_Eggs_Peanuts'),
(21, 'Shiitake & Hoisin Beef Burgers With Miso Mayonnaise & Roasted Sweet Potatoes', 'This customer favorite is a true stovetop trifecta: nonstick, heavy duty, and environmentally sound.', '4 Potato Buns\n2 cloves Garlic\n2 Scallions\n2 Sweet Potatoes\n½ lb Baby Bok Choy\n2 Tbsps Hoisin Sauce\n2 Tbsps Sweet White Miso Paste\n½ oz Dried Shiitake Mushrooms\n¼ cup Mayonnaise', '30min', 'Beef', '1204_FPM_Shiitake-Hoisin-Burger_94634_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '1204_ING_FPM_large_feature.png', '1204_FPM_Hoisin-Burgers_94894_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1204_FPM_Shiitake-Hoisin-Burger_18566_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1204_FPM_Shiitake-Hoisin-Burger_18547_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1204_FPM_Shiitake-Hoisin-Burger_18578_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Roast the Sweet Potatoes: Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then preheat to 450°F. Wash and dry the sweet potatoes; cut lengthwise into 1-inch wedges. Place on a sheet pan. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper; toss to coat. Arrange in an even layer, skin side down. Roast 22–24 minutes, or until browned and tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven.\n\nPrepare the Remaining Ingredients: While the sweet potatoes roast, wash and dry the remaining fresh produce. In a bowl, combine the mushrooms and 1 cup of hot water; let stand at least 10 minutes to rehydrate. Peel and finely chop the garlic; smash with the flat side of a knife into a paste. Cut off and discard the root ends of the scallions; thinly slice, separating the white bottoms and green tops. Cut off and discard the root end of the bok choy; thinly slice and place in a bowl. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper; toss to coat. Halve the buns. In a bowl, combine the miso paste and mayonnaise; season with salt and pepper.\n\nCook the Patties & Toast the Buns: In a large pan, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil over medium-high until hot. Add the patties and cook 3–4 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked to desired doneness. Transfer to a plate, leaving any fond in the pan. Working in batches if necessary, add the buns cut side down to the pan of reserved fond. Toast 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until lightly browned. Transfer to a work surface.\n\nAssemble & Serve: Divide the miso mayonnaise, cooked patties, and seasoned bok choy among the toasted buns. Serve with the roasted sweet potatoes and garnish with the sliced green scallion tops. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Shiitake_Hoisin_Beef_Burgers_with_Miso_Mayonnaise_Roasted_Sweet_Potatoes'),
(22, 'Roasted Pork & Broccoli With Apple, Cheese Sauce, & Garlic Breadcrumbs', 'To elevate the classic savory-sweet pairing, weʼre topping roasted pork with sautéed apple in this crowd-pleasing recipe. The pork and a side of broccoli, roasted on the same sheet pan, come together with a rich, warming fontina cheese sauce.', '3 Tbsps Panko Breadcrumbs 2 Tbsps All-Purpose Flour\n1 Tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar\n1 Tbsp Southern Spice Blend (Onion Powder, Garlic Powder, Ground Yellow Mustard, Smoked Paprika, & Cayenne Pepper)', '45min', 'Pork', '0108_2PRE08_Roasted-Pork_98452_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '0108_ING_2PRE08_large_feature.png', '0108_2PRE08_Roasted-Pork_98424_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PRE08_Roasted-Pork_98396_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PRE08_Roasted-Pork_98400_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PRE08_Roasted-Pork_98411_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PRE08_Roasted-Pork_98430_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PRE08_Roasted-Pork_98440_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Roast Pork & Broccoli: Preheat oven to 450°F and line a sheet pan with foil. Wash and dry produce. Trim broccoli into large pieces. Spread on one side of the sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt and pepper. Pat pork dry; season with salt, pepper, and spice blend. Place on the sheet pan, drizzle pork with olive oil, and roast 26–28 minutes until pork reaches 145°F and broccoli is browned. Let pork rest 5 minutes.\n\nPrepare Ingredients: Peel and finely chop garlic into a paste. Core and dice the apple. Small-dice the cheese.\n\nMake Garlic Breadcrumbs: Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a pan over medium-high. Add breadcrumbs and half the garlic paste; cook 2–3 minutes until golden. Transfer to a plate and season with salt and pepper.\n\nCook Apple: Heat a drizzle of olive oil in the same pan. Add diced apple and cook 3–5 minutes until slightly softened. Add vinegar and cook 30 seconds to 1 minute until evaporated. Transfer to a bowl and keep warm.\n\nMake Cheese Sauce: Heat 1½ tablespoons olive oil in the pan. Add flour and remaining garlic paste; cook 30 seconds to 1 minute. Add milk and ½ cup water and cook 2–3 minutes until thickened. Add diced cheese and cook 1–2 minutes until melted; season to taste.\n\nSlice Pork & Serve: Slice pork against the grain. Serve with roasted broccoli and cheese sauce. Top pork with cooked apples and garlic breadcrumbs. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Roasted_Pork_Broccoli_with_Apple_Cheese_Sauce_Garlic_Breadcrumbs'),
(23, 'General Tso\'s Chicken With Bok Choy & Jasmine Rice', 'In this quick-cooking spin on a takeout favorite, hoisin sauce, honey, sriracha, and sesame oil lend our chicken the sweet, spicy, and nutty flavors General Tsoʼs is known for. A light dusting of cornstarch on the chicken just before it hits the pan creates a delicately crispy exterior (and helps it soak up the irresistible sauce later).', '10 oz Chopped Chicken Breast 1 head Baby Bok Choy\n3⁄4 cup Jasmine Rice\n2 cloves Garlic\n1 Tbsp Rice Vinegar\n1 1-Inch Piece Ginger 1 tsp Sriracha\n1 Tbsp Honey\n1 Tbsp Sesame Oil\n1⁄4 cup Cornstarch\n2 Tbsps Hoisin Sauce', '35min', 'Chicken', '0101_2PRE07_General-Tsos-Chicken_97217_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '0101_ING_2PRE07_large_feature.png', '0101_2PRE07_General-Tsos-Chicken_18402_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PRE07_General-Tsos-Chicken_18405_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PRE07_General-Tsos-Chicken_18434_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PRE07_General-Tsos-Chicken_18422_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare the Ingredients: Remove honey from the refrigerator to bring to room temperature. In a medium pot, combine rice, a big pinch of salt, and 1½ cups water. Heat to boiling on high. Once boiling, cover and reduce heat to low. Cook 12–14 minutes, or until water is absorbed and rice is tender. Turn off heat, fluff with a fork, and keep warm.\n\nCoat & Cook the Chicken: Pat the chicken dry and season with salt and pepper. Add to a bowl with cornstarch and toss to coat. In a medium pan, heat a thin layer of oil over medium-high until hot. Add chicken in an even layer and cook 3–4 minutes without stirring, until lightly browned. Cook another 3–4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through. Transfer to a plate and keep warm.\n\nPrepare the Ingredients & Make the Sauce: Wash and dry produce. Cut off root end of bok choy and roughly chop. Peel and finely chop ginger. Peel and roughly chop garlic. In a bowl, combine hoisin sauce, vinegar, honey, sesame oil, 1 tablespoon water, and sriracha to taste.\n\nCook the Sauce & Bok Choy: Add bok choy, ginger, and garlic to the pan of fond; season with salt and pepper. Add 1 tablespoon olive oil if needed. Cook 2–3 minutes until softened and fragrant. Add the sauce and cook 30 seconds to 1 minute, stirring constantly, until combined.', 'Recipe_General_Tsos_Chicken_with_Bok_Choy_Jasmine_Rice'),
(24, 'Shrimp Fra Diavolo With Lumaca Rigata Pasta', 'When meal prep requires a delicate touch—think eggs over easy or a seared salmon fillet—ourculinary team grabs this even-heating, toxicant-free pan. The patented ceramic titanium coating', '6 oz Lumaca Rigata Pasta\n2 cloves Garlic\n1 8-Ounce Can Tomato Sauce\n1½ tsps Calabrian Chile Paste\n2 Tbsps Crème Fraîche\n2 Tbsps Sliced Roasted Almonds\n2 Tbsps Verjus Blanc\ntried-and-true', '60min', 'Pasta', '0101_2PF_Shrimp-Fra-Diavolo_97454_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_1-1_2PF_large_feature.png', '0101_2PF_Shrimp-Fra-Diavolo_01550_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PF_Shrimp-Fra-Diavolo_3260_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PF_Shrimp-Fra-Diavolo_3256_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PF_Shrimp-Fra-Diavolo_3270_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PF_Shrimp-Fra-Diavolo_3282_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare the Ingredients & Cook the Shrimp: Fill a medium pot with water; add a big pinch of salt and heat to boiling on high. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut out and discard the core of the cabbage; thinly slice the leaves. Peel and roughly chop the garlic. Pat the shrimp dry with paper towels; season with salt and pepper. In a medium pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high until hot. Add the seasoned shrimp; cook, stirring occasionally, 3–4 minutes, or until opaque and cooked through. Transfer to a plate and keep warm.\n\nCook the Cabbage: Add the sliced cabbage to the pan of reserved fond; season with salt and pepper. (If the pan seems dry, add a drizzle of olive oil.) Cook, stirring occasionally, 2–3 minutes, or until slightly softened. Add the verjus and ¼ cup of water; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally and scraping up any fond, 3–5 minutes, until cabbage has softened and water has cooked off. Transfer to the plate of cooked shrimp. Wipe out the pan.\n\nCook the Pasta: While the cabbage cooks, add the pasta to the pot of boiling water. Cook, stirring occasionally, 9–11 minutes, or until al dente. Reserve ½ cup of the pasta cooking water, then drain thoroughly.\n\nMake the Sauce: In the same pan, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil over medium-high until hot. Add the chopped garlic; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, 30 seconds to 1 minute, until softened and fragrant. Add the tomato sauce, 1/3 cup of water, and chile paste to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 4–5 minutes, until thickened. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\nFinish & Serve: Add the cooked pasta, cooked shrimp, and cabbage, along with half the reserved pasta water to the pan. Cook, stirring vigorously, 1–2 minutes, or until coated. If the sauce seems dry, gradually add the remaining pasta water to reach desired consistency. Turn off the heat, stir in the crème fraîche, and season with salt and pepper. Top with almonds and a drizzle of olive oil. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Shrimp_Fra_Diavolo_with_Lumaca_Rigata_Pasta'),
(25, 'Roasted Squash Curry With Crispy Mung Beans & Jasmine Rice', 'In this recipe, veggie curry gets a unique lift from spaghetti squash—oven-roasted, then broken into pasta-like strands with a fork. Weʼre finishing our squash and bok choy in a sauce made with fresh aromatics and two well-balanced pantry ingredients: spicy yellow curry paste and cooling coconut milk. A garnish of dried mung beans brings it all together with exciting crunch.', '1⁄2 cup Jasmine Rice\n13⁄4 cups Light Coconut Milk 1 Lime\n1 Yellow Onion\n1 bunch Mint\n2 Tbsps Dried Mung Beans 11⁄2 Tbsps Yellow Curry Paste 1 1-Inch Piece Ginger\n1 Tbsp Sugar\n1⁄2 lb Baby Bok Choy', '30min', 'Vegetarian', '1127_2PV3_Vegetable-Curry_74908_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_11-27_2PV3_large_feature.png', '1127_2PV3_Vegetable-Curry_18480_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_2PV3_Broccoli-Curry_94348_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_2PV3_Vegetable-Curry_18452_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_2PV3_Broccoli-Curry_94335_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1127_2PV3_Vegetable-Curry_18484_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Roast the Squash: Preheat oven to 450°F. Wash and dry produce. Carefully halve the squash lengthwise and scoop out the seeds. Place cut side up in a baking dish, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper, then place cut side down. Add ¼ inch water to the dish and roast 32–35 minutes until tender.\n\nCook the Rice: In a small pot, combine rice, lime leaf, a pinch of salt, and 1 cup water. Heat to boiling, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook 12–14 minutes until water is absorbed. Remove lime leaf, fluff rice, and keep warm.\n\nPrepare Remaining Ingredients: Peel and thinly slice the onion. Peel and finely chop ginger. Quarter the lime. Thinly slice the bok choy crosswise. Pick mint leaves.\n\nCook the Aromatics: In a large pan, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium-high. Add onion, season with salt and pepper, and cook 3–4 minutes. Add ginger and cook 1–2 minutes. Add coconut milk, sugar, and curry paste to desired spice level; season with salt and pepper. Cook 3–4 minutes until slightly thickened; adjust seasoning.\n\nFinish the Curry & Serve: Scrape roasted squash into strands and add to the curry along with bok choy. Cook 2–3 minutes until softened. Turn off heat and stir in juice of 2 lime wedges. Serve the curry over rice and garnish with mung beans and mint leaves, with remaining lime wedges on the side. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Roasted_Squash_Curry_with_Crispy_Mung_Beans_Jasmine_Rice'),
(26, 'Tuscan Chicken & Green Lentil Stew With Goat Cheese', 'In this comforting cold-weather recipe, weʼre serving Tuscan-spiced chicken over tender green lentils and vegetables cooked in a light, savory tomato broth. Capers and crushed red pepper add briny flavor and a touch of heat to cut through the rich, earthy stew. (Chefs, rinsing the lentils after cooking removes excess starch, resulting in a more delicate flavor.', '2 Boneless, Skinless Chicken Breasts\n2 Carrots \n1 Red Onion \n2 cloves Garlic \n1⁄2 cup French Green Lentils \n1 bunch Collard Greens \n2 Tbsps Tomato Paste \n1⁄4 tsp Crushed Red Pepper Flakes \n1 Tbsp Capers \n1 Tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar \n2 Tbsps Crumbled Goat Cheese \n1 Tbsp Tuscan Spice Blend (Ground Fennel Seeds, Whole Fennel Seeds, Ground Rosemary, & Ground Sage)', '45min', 'Chicken', '0101_2PP_Chicken-Lentil-Stew_100567_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_1-1_2PP_large_feature.png', '0101_2PP_Chicken-Lentil-Stew_18500_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PP_Chicken-Lentil-Stew_18453_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PP_Chicken-Lentil-Stew_18494_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PP_Chicken-Lentil-Stew_18508_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_2PP_Chicken-Lentil-Stew_18520_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Cook the Lentils: Preheat oven to 450°F. Heat a medium pot of salted water to boiling. Add lentils and cook uncovered 27–29 minutes until tender. Drain, rinse under warm water, return to the pot, cover, and keep warm.\n\nPrepare the Ingredients: Wash and dry produce. Peel and thinly slice the onion. Peel and roughly chop garlic. Peel and medium-dice the carrots. Roughly chop capers. Remove collard green stems and roughly chop leaves.\n\nCook the Chicken: Pat chicken dry; season with salt, pepper, and half the spice blend. Heat 2 teaspoons olive oil in a large pan over medium-high. Add chicken and cook 5–7 minutes per side until browned and cooked through. Transfer chicken to a cutting board, leaving fond in the pan.\n\nCook the Vegetables: Add onion, garlic, and carrots to the pan; season with salt and pepper. If dry, add 2 teaspoons olive oil. Cook 4–5 minutes until softened. Add tomato paste, capers, remaining spice blend, and red pepper flakes to taste; cook 30 seconds to 1 minute. Add collard greens and 2 cups water; season. Cook 8–9 minutes, stirring occasionally, until wilted and broth thickened. Turn off heat.\n\nSlice the Chicken & Serve: Slice chicken. Add lentils and vinegar to the vegetables; stir. Serve topped with sliced chicken and garnish with cheese. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Tuscan_Chicken_Green_Lentil_Stew_with_Goat_Cheese'),
(27, 'Crispy Fish Sandwiches With Tartar Sauce & Roasted Sweet Potato Wedges', 'These sandwiches highlight wild Alaskan pollock—flavored with aromatic seasonings, coated with panko breadcrumbs, and pan-fried for a golden-brown crust. In classic fashion, a tangy, mayo-based tartar sauce perfectly balances the fish.', '21 oz Wild Alaskan Pollock Fillets 2 Cage-Free Farm Eggs\n2 Tbsps Sweet Pickle Relish\n1 Romaine Lettuce Heart\n1 Tbsp Weeknight Hero Spice Blend (Garlic Powder, Onion Powder, Smoked Paprika, & Whole Dried Parsley)\n11⁄4 cups Panko Breadcrumbs 1⁄4 cup Creamy Mustard Sauce', '55min', 'Fish', '0101_FPF_Crispy-Wild-Alaskan-Pollock_97377_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '0101_ING_FPF_large_feature.png', '0101_FPF_Crispy-Wild-Alaskan-Pollock_3170_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPF_Crispy-Wild-Alaskan-Pollock_3148_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPF_Crispy-Wild-Alaskan-Pollock_3161_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPF_Crispy-Wild-Alaskan-Pollock_3182_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPF_Crispy-Wild-Alaskan-Pollock_3185_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPF_Crispy-Wild-Alaskan-Pollock_3204_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Roast the Sweet Potatoes: Place an oven rack in the center of the oven and preheat to 450°F. Wash and dry the produce. Cut the sweet potatoes into 1-inch-wide wedges. Place on a sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt and pepper; toss to coat. Arrange in an even layer, skin side down. Roast 27–29 minutes, or until browned and tender when pierced with a fork. Transfer to a plate and keep warm.\n\nPrepare Remaining Ingredients & Make the Sauce: Cut off and discard the root end of the lettuce; thinly slice the leaves. Halve the rolls. In a bowl, combine the mayonnaise, creamy mustard sauce, and sweet pickle relish; season with salt and pepper. Pat the fish fillets dry and halve crosswise.\n\nBread & Cook the Fish: Season the fish with salt, pepper, and spice blend. Crack the eggs into a bowl, season with salt and pepper, and beat until smooth. Place breadcrumbs on a plate and season with salt and pepper. Coat each fish piece in egg, letting excess drip off, then into breadcrumbs, pressing to adhere.\n\nPan-Fry the Fish: In a large pan, heat a thin layer of oil over medium-high until hot. Working in batches, add the breaded fish. Cook 2–3 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through. Add more oil as needed. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate and season with salt and pepper.\n\nToast the Rolls: Place rolls on the same sheet pan, cut side up. Drizzle with olive oil. Toast in the oven 4–5 minutes, or until lightly browned.\n\nAssemble the Sandwiches & Serve: Spread the sauce on the rolls, add the cooked fish and sliced lettuce, and close the sandwiches. Serve with roasted sweet potatoes. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Crispy_Fish_Sandwiches_with_Tartar_Sauce_Roasted_Sweet_Potato_Wedges'),
(28, 'Hoisin-Glazed Pork Chops With Stir-Fried Vegetables & Wonton Noodles', 'Delightfully chewy wonton noodles tossed in a nutty, savory sauce are a delicious accompaniment to these pork chops. For depth of flavor, weʼre pan-searing the pork chops, then glazing them with barbecue-like hoisin, whose sweetness perfectly matches bites of sautéed carrots in the noodles.', '4 Boneless, Center-Cut Pork Chops 2 Carrots\n1 bunch Chives\n2 Tbsps Tahini\n2 Tbsps Soy Sauce\n3⁄4 lb Fresh Wonton Noodles 2 tsps Sambal Oelek\n1 1-Inch Piece Ginger\n1⁄4 cup Hoisin Sauce', '30min', 'Pork', '0101_FPM_Pork-Chops_97303_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '0101_ING_FPM_large_feature.png', '0101_FPM_Pork-Chops_18526_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPM_Pork-Chops_18450_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPM_Pork-Chops_18467_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPM_Pork-Chops_18441_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPM_Pork-Chops_18484_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0101_FPM_Pork-Chops_18487_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare the Ingredients: Fill a medium pot with water; add a pinch of salt and heat to boiling on high. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Peel and finely chop the ginger. Cut out and discard the core of the cabbage; thinly slice the leaves. Peel the carrots and thinly slice into rounds. Thinly slice the chives.\n\nCook the Vegetables: In a large pan, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium-high until hot. Add the chopped ginger, sliced cabbage, and sliced carrots; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 4–5 minutes, or until softened and fragrant. Transfer to a bowl and cover with foil to keep warm. Rinse and wipe out the pan.\n\nCook & Glaze the Pork Chops: Pat the pork chops dry; season both sides with salt and pepper. In the same pan, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil over medium-high until hot. Add the chops; cook 3–5 minutes on the first side until browned. Flip and cook 2–3 minutes until lightly browned. Add hoisin sauce and ¼ cup water. Cook, spooning glaze over the pork, 2–3 minutes until coated and cooked through. Turn off heat.\n\nPrepare the Sauce for Noodles: In a bowl, whisk together soy sauce, tahini, vinegar, and sambal oelek to taste; season with salt and pepper.\n\nCook the Noodles: Carefully separate the noodles and add to the pot of boiling water. Cook 2–4 minutes, or until tender. Drain thoroughly and return to the pot.\n\nFinish the Noodles & Serve: Add the cooked vegetables, sauce, and ¼ cup water to the pot of noodles. Cook over medium-high, stirring constantly, 30 seconds to 1 minute until combined. Serve with glazed pork chops and pan glaze; garnish with chives. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_HoisinGlazed_Pork_Chops_with_StirFried_Vegetables_Wonton_Noodles'),
(29, 'Top Chef Seared Grassfed Steaks With Sweet Chili-Glazed Vegetables', 'In this recipe, inspired by our Quickfire Challenge from Top Chef Season 15 on Bravo, simple grassfed steaks and rice get a sweet, tart, and spicy lift from glazed mushrooms    and bok choy. Sliced radishes, softened a bit with lime juice, finish the dish off with subtle crunch.', '2 Grassfed Strip Steaks \n4 oz Cremini Mushrooms \n1 1-Inch Piece Ginger \n2 Tbsps Sweet Chili Sauce', '35min', 'Beef', '0108_FPM_Seared-Steaks_97965_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '0108_ING_FPM_large_feature.png', '0108_FPM_Seared-Steaks_97909_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPM_Seared-Steaks_97920_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPM_Seared-Steaks_97914_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPM_Seared-Steaks_97936_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPM_Seared-Steaks_97945_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare Ingredients & Make the Glaze: Wash and dry produce. Quarter the mushrooms. Peel and thinly slice the shallot. Peel and finely chop the ginger. Roughly chop the bok choy. Quarter the lime. Thinly slice the radishes into rounds and place in a bowl with juice of 1 lime wedge, a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper; stir to coat. In a separate bowl, combine ponzu sauce, sweet chili sauce, sugar, ¼ cup water, and soy marinade to taste.\n\nMake the Rice: In a medium pot, combine rice, a pinch of salt, and 1½ cups water. Bring to a boil on high. Once boiling, cover and reduce heat to low. Cook 12–14 minutes until water is absorbed. Fluff and keep warm.\n\nCook the Steaks: Pat steaks dry; season with salt and pepper. Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large pan over medium-high. Add steaks and cook 4–5 minutes per side for medium-rare, or to desired doneness. Transfer to a cutting board and rest 5 minutes. Leave fond in the pan.\n\nCook the Vegetables: Add 1 tablespoon olive oil to the pan. Add mushrooms in an even layer and cook 3–4 minutes without stirring until browned. Add shallot and ginger; cook 30 seconds to 1 minute until fragrant.\n\nSlice Steaks & Serve: Slice steaks against the grain. Serve with rice and glazed vegetables. Garnish with marinated radishes, draining before adding. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Top_Chef_Seared_Grassfed_Steaks_with_Sweet_Chili-Glazed_Vegetables'),
(30, 'Honey-Butter Barramundi With Za\'atar Roasted Vegetables', 'This Middle Eastern recipe pairs crispy barramundi—served in a family-friendly pan sauce of honey and butter—with a medley of winter vegetables. For savory, herby flavor, weʼre seasoning the vegetables with zaʼatar before roasting them.', '4 Skin-On Barramundi Fillets 1⁄2 cup Plain Greek Yogurt 11⁄8 lbs Yukon Gold Potatoes\n1 Tbsp Za\'atar Seasoning (Ground Sumac, Sesame Seeds, Salt, Ground Thyme, Whole Dried Oregano, & Crushed Aleppo Pepper)', '30min', 'Fish', '0108_FPF_Barramundi_0304_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '0108_ING_FPF_AR_large_feature.png', '0108_FPF_Barramundi_0216_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPF_Barramundi_0269_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPF_Barramundi_98216_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPF_Barramundi_98243_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPF_Barramundi_98255_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPF_Barramundi_0290_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare the Ingredients: Remove honey from the refrigerator to bring to room temperature. Place an oven rack in the center and preheat to 450°F. Wash and dry produce. Halve the potatoes; cut crosswise into ¼-inch pieces. Peel carrots; cut into ½-inch pieces. Trim the radishes and quarter lengthwise, then halve crosswise. Quarter and deseed the lemon. Peel and finely chop the garlic. Roughly chop parsley.\n\nRoast the Vegetables: Place potatoes and carrots on a sheet pan, drizzle with 1 tablespoon olive oil, season with salt, pepper, and za’atar, and toss to coat. Roast 12–14 minutes. Meanwhile, toss radish pieces with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Add radishes to the sheet pan and roast another 10–12 minutes, until tender. Remove from oven and top with juice of 2 lemon wedges.\n\nMake the Yogurt Sauce: Combine yogurt, juice of remaining lemon wedges, 1 tablespoon olive oil, and garlic paste to taste. Season with salt and pepper.\n\nCook the Fish: After vegetables have roasted for about 10 minutes, pat the fish dry; season with salt and pepper. In a large pan, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil over medium-high. Add fillets, skin side down; cook 4–6 minutes until browned. Flip, add butter, and cook 2–3 minutes, spooning butter over the fish. Transfer to a plate, leaving the butter and fond in the pan.\n\nMake the Pan Sauce: Add honey and 2 tablespoons water to the pan of melted butter. Cook 30 seconds to 1 minute, stirring frequently, until slightly thickened. Season with salt and pepper.\n\nServe the Dish: Serve the fish with roasted vegetables and yogurt sauce. Top fish with pan sauce and garnish with parsley. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_HoneyButter_Barramundi_with_Zaatar_Roasted_Vegetables'),
(31, 'Kale & Ricotta Quiche With Romaine, Apple, & Almond Salad', 'This crowd-pleasing quiche showcases a rich, eggy filling made with ricotta and cream —balanced by hearty sautéed kale. On the side, weʼre serving a refreshing salad of crisp romaine and apple, wrapped in a creamy lemon dressing.', '4 Cage-Free Farm Eggs\n1 cup Part-Skim Ricotta Cheese 1 Romaine Lettuce Heart\n2 Tbsps Sliced Roasted Almonds\n1 Tbsp Cajun Spice Blend (Smoked Paprika, Ground Yellow Mustard, Onion Powder, Garlic Powder, Whole Dried Oregano, Whole Dried Thyme, & Cayenne Pepper)\n2 Tbsps Crème Fraîche', '40min', 'Vegetarian', '0108_FPV_Kale-Quiche_97823_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '0108_ING_FPV_large_feature.png', '0108_FPV_Kale-Quiche_97642_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPV_Kale-Quiche_97717_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPV_Kale-Quiche_97807_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPV_Kale-Quiche_97774_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPV_Kale-Quiche_97802_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPV_Kale-Quiche_97741_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare the Ingredients: Preheat oven to 425°F. Wash and dry produce. Peel and roughly chop garlic. Peel and thinly slice shallot. Remove and discard kale stems; roughly chop the leaves. Quarter and deseed the lemon.\n\nCook the Kale & Aromatics: In a large pan, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium-high until hot. Add garlic and shallot; season with salt and pepper. Cook 1–2 minutes until softened. Add chopped kale, heavy cream, and ¼ cup water; season with salt and pepper. Cook 4–5 minutes until kale is wilted and liquid mostly evaporated. Turn off heat.\n\nPrepare the Filling: Crack eggs into a bowl. Add ricotta, juice of 1 lemon wedge, and spice blend; season with salt and pepper. Whisk to combine, then stir in cooked kale.\n\nAssemble & Bake the Quiche: Place pie crust (still in the tin) on a sheet pan. Pour in filling and season with salt and pepper. Bake 24–26 minutes, until crust is browned and filling is set. Let stand at least 5 minutes.\n\nPrepare the Salad Ingredients: Quarter and core the apple; thinly slice. Toss in a bowl with lemon juice to prevent browning. Chop the lettuce. In another bowl, combine crème fraîche, lemon juice, and olive oil; season with salt and pepper.\n\nMake the Salad & Serve: Just before serving, add the apple and lettuce to the dressing; toss to coat. Serve quiche with salad and garnish with almonds. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Kale_Ricotta_Quiche_with_Romaine_Apple_Almond_Salad'),
(32, 'Mexican-Spiced Barramundi With Kale, Sweet Potato, & Avocado Salad', 'A vibrant, feel-good plate where flaky barramundi is coated in warm Mexican spices and seared until perfectly crisp. It’s paired with a hearty kale and roasted sweet potato salad, tossed lightly to bring out its natural sweetness, then finished with creamy avocado for richness.', '2 Skin-On Barramundi Fillets \n1 Lime \n1 Clove Garlic \n1 Clementine\n2 Sweet Potatoes\n1 Jalapeño Pepper\n1 Avocado\n1 Bunch Kale\n2 Tbsps Pepitas \n1 Tbsp Mexican Spice Blend*\n\n* Ancho Chile Powder, Smoked Paprika, Garlic Powder, Ground Cumin, & Dried Mexican Oregano\n', '35min', 'Fish', '0108_2PF_Barramundi_98380_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_1-8_2PF_large_feature.png', '0108_2PF_Barramundi_98342_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PF_Barramundi_98337_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PF_Barramundi_98347_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PF_Barramundi_98356_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PF_Barramundi_98362_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_2PF_Barramundi_98367_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare & Roast the Sweet Potatoes: Place an oven rack in the center and preheat to 450°F. Wash and dry produce. Halve sweet potatoes lengthwise, then slice crosswise into ¼-inch pieces. Spread on a sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt, pepper, and half the spice blend. Roast 20–22 minutes, flipping halfway through, until lightly browned.\n\nPrepare the Remaining Ingredients: Quarter the lime. Halve the avocado; thinly slice one half and toss with lime juice, salt, and pepper. Mash the other half in a bowl and season with salt and pepper. Peel and finely chop the garlic to a paste. Remove clementine rind with a peeler and mince to get 2 teaspoons zest. Halve the clementine and squeeze juice into a bowl. Remove kale stems and thinly slice leaves. Finely chop the pepper.\n\nMake the Dressing & Marinate the Kale: To the mashed avocado, add garlic paste, clementine juice and zest, 3 tablespoons olive oil, and chopped pepper to taste. Season with salt and pepper and add sliced kale. Stir to coat and let marinate at least 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n\nToast the Pepitas: In a medium pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high. Add pepitas; season with salt and pepper. Toast 2–3 minutes, stirring often, until fragrant. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.\n\nCook the Fish: Pat fish dry; season with salt, pepper, and remaining spice blend. In the same pan, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium-high. Add fillets skin side down; cook 3–5 minutes until skin is crisp. Flip and cook 2–3 minutes more until cooked through.\n\nMake the Salad & Serve: Add roasted sweet potatoes to the marinated kale and toss. Serve salad with fish and sliced avocado, then garnish with toasted pepitas. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_MexicanSpiced_Barramundi_with_Kale_Sweet_Potato_Avocado_Salad'),
(33, 'Tilapia & Black Lentil Salad With Lemon Pan Sauce', 'In this dish, weʼre putting a twist on Italian gremolata: adding pickled peppers to the classic parsley, garlic, and lemon condiment. The bright, tangy flavors perk up a hearty salad of black lentils and roasted broccoli. Weʼre also using lemon juice as the base for an easy pan sauce to serve over our seared tilapia.', '1⁄2 cup Black Beluga Lentils \n2 cloves Garlic \n1 Lemon \n1⁄2 lb Broccoli \n1 bunch Parsley \n2 Tbsps Butter \n1 oz Golden Or Red Sweet Piquante Peppers \n1 Tbsp Capers', '35min', 'Fish', '1225_2PF_Tilapia_74912_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '1225_ING_2PF_large_feature.png', '1225_2PF_Tilapia_18754_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PF_Tilapia_18757_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PF_Tilapia_18753_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PF_Tilapia_18758_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PF_Tilapia_18762_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PF_Tilapia_18760_copy_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Cook the Lentils: Place oven rack in center and preheat to 450°F. Heat a medium saucepan of salted water to boiling. Add lentils and cook uncovered 24–26 minutes until tender. Drain, rinse with warm water, return to pot, and keep warm.\n\nPrepare & Roast Broccoli: Wash and dry produce. Trim bottom ½ inch of broccoli stems; cut into small pieces. Spread on a sheet pan, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt and pepper. Roast 15–17 minutes until browned and tender.\n\nPrepare Remaining Ingredients: Peel garlic. Roughly chop one clove; finely chop and smash the other to a paste. Zest the lemon to get 2 teaspoons. Quarter and deseed the lemon. Roughly chop peppers. Finely chop parsley. Make gremolata by combining lemon zest, chopped peppers, half the parsley, juice of 2 lemon wedges, olive oil, and garlic paste to taste.\n\nCook the Fish: Pat fish dry; season with salt and pepper. Heat 2 teaspoons olive oil in a large pan over medium-high. Add fish and cook 2–3 minutes per side until browned and cooked through. Transfer to a plate, leaving fond in pan.\n\nMake the Pan Sauce: Add capers, chopped garlic, butter, and olive oil to the pan. Season with salt and pepper and cook 1–2 minutes until fragrant and browned. Turn off heat and stir in juice of remaining lemon wedges.\n\nFinish Lentils & Serve: Add roasted broccoli and gremolata to the lentils; stir and season to taste. Serve topped with fish and spoon pan sauce over the top. Garnish with remaining parsley. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Tilapia_Black_Lentil_Salad_with_Lemon_Pan_Sauce'),
(34, 'Thai Curry Chicken With Carrots & Bok Choy', 'In tonightʼs dish, the spicy and aromatic flavors of yellow curry paste—a Thai staple— shine through a lightly sweet coconut milk broth. Sautéed chicken, carrots, and bok choy give the curry plenty of hearty texture, while fluffy rice eagerly soaks up all the complex flavors. (Chefs, this curry paste packs a punch of heat, so be sure to use only as much as youʼd like!)', '10 oz Chopped Chicken Breast \n13⁄4 cups Light Coconut Milk \n3 Carrots \n1 Lime \n1 head Baby Bok Choy \n1⁄2 cup Dried Shiitake Mushrooms \n2 tsps Golden Mountain Sauce \n11⁄2 Tbsps Yellow Curry Paste', '45min', 'Chicken', '1218_2PRE07_Thai-Curry-Chicken_96739_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '1218_ING_2PRE07_large_feature.png', '1218_2PRE07_Thai-Curry-Chicken_18444_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_2PRE07_Thai-Curry-Chicken_18470_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_2PRE07_Thai-Curry-Chicken_18455_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_2PRE07_Thai-Curry-Chicken_18459_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1218_2PRE07_Thai-Curry-Chicken_18488_1_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Prepare Ingredients & Rehydrate Mushrooms: Wash and dry produce. Place mushrooms in 1 cup warm water and soak at least 10 minutes. Peel and thinly slice carrots. Slice bok choy stems; roughly chop leaves separately. Quarter the lime.\n\nCook the Rice: In a small pot, combine rice, a pinch of salt, and 1½ cups water; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low, and cook 12–14 minutes until tender. Fluff and keep warm.\n\nCook the Chicken: Pat chicken dry; season with salt and pepper. Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large pan over medium-high. Add chicken and cook 3–4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned. Transfer to a plate, leaving fond.\n\nChop Mushrooms & Start the Curry: Drain and roughly chop the mushrooms. Heat 2 teaspoons olive oil in the pan of fond. Add sliced carrots and curry paste to desired spice level; season with salt and pepper. Cook 1–2 minutes until fragrant.\n\nFinish Curry & Serve: Add browned chicken, bok choy stems, Golden Mountain sauce, chopped mushrooms, and coconut milk. Simmer 4–5 minutes until slightly reduced. Add bok choy leaves and cook 2–3 minutes until wilted. Turn off heat and add juice of 2 lime wedges. Serve with rice and remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_Thai_Curry_Chicken_with_Carrots_Bok_Choy'),
(35, 'Beef Medallions & Mushroom Sauce With Mashed Potatoes', 'In this easy recipe, inspired by steak Diane (an American restaurant classic), we\'re searing beef medallions, then using the fond in the pan to make a rich, bright mushroom sauce for spooning on top. Garlic mashed potatoes and sautee\'d kale make for delicious, simple sides.', 'Potatoes, large-diced\r\nGarlic, 2 cloves (1 smashed, 1 chopped)\r\nShallot, 1 small, thinly sliced\r\nKale, 1 bunch\r\nMushrooms, about 4 oz, thinly sliced\r\nBeef, about 2 portions\r\nButter, 1–2 tablespoons\r\nOlive oil, about 3–4 tablespoons', '45min', 'Beef', '0101_2PM_Steak-Diane_97315_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_1-1_2PM_large_feature.png', '0101_2PM_Steaks-Diane_18414_WEB_high_feature.jpg\r\n0101_2PM_Steaks-Diane_18506_WEB_high_feature.jpg\r\n0101_2PM_Steaks-Diane_18516_WEB_high_feature.jpg\r\n0101_2PM_Steaks-Diane_18524_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Heat a medium pot of salted water to boiling on high. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Large dice the potatoes. Peel the garlic. Using the flat side of your knife, smash 1 clove to flatten. Roughly chop the remaining clove. Peel and thinly slice the shallot. Remove and discard the stems of the kale; roughly chop the leaves. Thinly slice the mushrooms.\r\n\r\nAdd the diced potatoes and smashed garlic to the pot of boiling water and cook 13 to 15 minutes, or until tender when pierced with a fork. Turn off the heat. Drain thoroughly and return to the pot. Add half the butter and a drizzle of olive oil. Using a fork, mash to your desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Cover to keep warm.\r\n\r\nWhile the potatoes cook, in a large pan, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. Add the sliced shallot; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 1 to 2 minutes, or until softened. Add the chopped kale and 1/4 cup of water; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, 3 to 4 minutes, or until the kale has wilted and the water has cooked off. Transfer to a bowl and season with salt and pepper to taste. Cover with aluminum foil to keep warm. Rinse and wipe out the pan.\r\n\r\nWhile the potatoes continue to cook, pat the beef dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper on both sides. In the same pan, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. Add the seasoned beef and cook 2 to 3 minutes per side for medium-rare, or until browned and cooked to your desired degree of doneness. Leaving any browned bits (or fond) in the pan, transfer to a plate and let rest for at least 5 minutes.', 'Recipe_Beef_Medallions_Mushroom_Sauce_with_Mashed_Potatoes'),
(36, 'Broccoli & Basil Pesto Sandwiches With Romaine & Citrus Salad', 'These Italian focaccia sandwiches are layered with broccoli, three cheeses, and a savory basil, cashew, and pine nut pesto, then baked in the oven to meld all the bright, aromatic flavors. On the side, we\'re serving a refreshing salad of romaine and seasonal clementine.', '1 Piece Focaccia Bread\r\n1 8-Ounce Can Tomato Sauce\r\n1/2 lb Fresh Mozzarella Cheese\r\n2 Clementines\r\n2 cloves Garlic\r\n2 Romaine Lettuce Hearts\r\n1 lb Broccoli \r\n1 oz Golden Or Red Sweet Piquante Peppers\r\n2 Tbsps Creme Fraiche\r\n1 Tbsp Dijon Mustard\r\n1/2 cup Basil & Cashew Pesto (Contains Pine Nuts)\r\n1/3 cup Shaved Parmesan Cheese\r\n1 Tbsp Italian Seasoning', '45min', 'Vegetarian', '1225_FPV_Pesto_-Broccoli-Sandwich_74916_WEB_SQ_hi_res.jpg', '1225_ING_FPV_large_feature.png', '1225_FPV_Pesto-Broccoli-Sandwich_18814_WEB_high_feature.jpg\r\n1225_FPV_Pesto-Broccoli-Sandwich_18818_WEB_high_feature.jpg\r\n1225_FPV_Pesto-Broccoli-Sandwich_18819_WEB_high_feature.jpg\r\n1225_FPV_Pesto-Broccoli-Sandwich_18821_WEB_high_feature.jpg\r\n1225_FPV_Pesto-Broccoli-Sandwich_18823_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then preheat to 475 degrees. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut off and discard the bottom 1/2 inch of the broccoli stem; cut the broccoli into small pieces, keeping the florets intact. Peel and roughly chop the garlic. Halve the focaccia. Grate the asiago cheese on the large side of a box grater. Tear the mozzarella cheese into small pieces. In a bowl, combine the tomato sauce and Italian seasoning; season with salt and pepper to taste.\r\n\r\nIn a large pan (nonstick, if you have one), heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. Add the broccoli pieces; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 to 4 minutes, or until slightly softened. Add the chopped garlic; cook, stirring frequently, 1 to 2 minutes, or until slightly softened and fragrant. Add 1/2 cup of water; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 4 to 5 minutes, or until the broccoli has softened and the water has cooked off. Turn off the heat.\r\n\r\nLine a sheet pan with foil. Place the halved focaccia on the foil, cut side up; drizzle with olive oil. Top with the seasoned tomato sauce. Top the focaccia bottom with the grated asiago cheese, half the mozzarella cheese, and the cooked broccoli. Evenly top the broccoli with the remaining mozzarella cheese and pesto (stirring before adding). Season both focaccia halves with salt and pepper. Bake, rotating the sheet pan halfway through, 11 to 13 minutes, or until lightly browned and the cheese has melted. Remove from the oven; let stand for at least 2 minutes. Transfer to a cutting board.\r\n\r\nWhile the focaccia bakes, cut off and discard the root end of the lettuce; roughly chop the leaves. Place in a large bowl. Roughly chop the peppers. Halve 1 clementine crosswise; squeeze the juice into a bowl, straining out any seeds. Peel the remaining clementine; separate into segments. To make the dressing, add the creme fraeeche, mustard, and 1 tablespoon of water to the bowl of clementine juice. Slowly whisk in a drizzle of olive oil until combined; season with salt and pepper to taste.\r\n\r\nJust before serving, add the clementine segments, chopped peppers, and dressing to the bowl of chopped lettuce. Toss to thoroughly coat. Season with salt and pepper to taste.', 'Recipe_Broccoli_Basil_Pesto_Sandwiches_with_Romaine_Citrus_Salad'),
(37, 'Bucatini & Tomato Sauce With Roasted Broccoli', 'Made with petite datterini tomatoes, the sauce for tonight\'s bucatini highlights briny olives and capers, hot red pepper flakes, and savory Grana Padano cheese. We\'re mixing in roasted broccoli for contrasting texture and nutty-sweet flavor.', '6 oz Bucatini Pasta\r\n1 14-Ounce Can Datterini Tomatoes\r\n2 cloves Garlic\r\n2 Tbsps Butter\r\n1 Tbsp Capers\r\n1 lb Broccoli\r\n3/4 oz Grana Padano Cheese\r\n1 oz Kalamata Olives\r\n1/4 tsp Crushed Red Pepper Flakes\r\n1 Tbsp Italian Seasoning', '45min', 'Pasta', '1225_2PV1_Bucatini_100082_SQ_hi_res.jpg', 'ING_12-25_2PV1_large_feature.png', '1225_2PV1_Bucatini_18441_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV1_Bucatini_18402_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV1_Bucatini_18423_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n1225_2PV1_Bucatini_18448_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then preheat to 450 degrees. Heat a large pot of salted water to boiling on high. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut off and discard the bottom 1/2 inch of the broccoli stem; cut the broccoli into small pieces. Place on a sheet pan. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt, pepper, and up to half the Italian seasoning (you will have extra); toss to coat. Arrange in an even layer. Roast 22 to 24 minutes, or until browned and tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven.\r\n\r\nWhile the broccoli roasts, peel and roughly chop the garlic. Using the flat side of your knife, smash the olives; remove and discard the pits, then roughly chop. Grate the cheese on the small side of a box grater.\r\n\r\nWhile the broccoli continues to roast, add the pasta to the pot of boiling water and cook 8 to 10 minutes, or until al dente (still slightly firm to the bite). Turn off the heat. Reserving 1/2 cup of the pasta cooking water, drain thoroughly and return to the pot.\r\n\r\nWhile the pasta cooks, in a medium pan, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. Add the chopped garlic, capers, and as much of the red pepper flakes as you\'d like, depending on how spicy you\'d like the dish to be; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until fragrant. Add the tomatoes and chopped olives; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally and gently crushing the tomatoes with the back of a spoon, 6 to 7 minutes, or until thickened. Turn off the heat and season with salt and pepper to taste.', 'Recipe_Bucatini_Tomato_Sauce_with_Roasted_Broccoli');
INSERT INTO `idm232_recipe_sheet` (`id`, `Title`, `Bio`, `Ingredients`, `Cook_Time`, `Filter`, `Recipe_Img`, `Ingredients_Img`, `Steps_Img`, `Recipe`, `Folder`) VALUES
(38, 'Parmesan-Crusted Chicken With Mashed Sweet Potatoes & Roasted Broccoli', 'For this comforting autumn dinner, we\'re seasoning half chickens with the classic flavors of garlic, onion, and smoked paprika, then roasting them along with sweet potatoes and Brussels sprouts. The rich chicken finds delicious contrast in a tart-sweet compote.', '4 Boneless, Skinless Chicken Breasts\r\n1/4 cup All-Purpose Flour\r\n1/2 cup Grated Parmesan Cheese\r\n1 Tbsp Weeknight Hero Spice Blend', '45min', 'Chicken', '0108_FPP_Baked-Parmesan-Chicken_98333_WEB_Center_hi_res.jpg', '0108_ING_FPP_large_feature.png', '0108_FPP_Baked-Parmesan-Chicken_98274_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPP_Baked-Parmesan-Chicken_98310_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPP_Baked-Parmesan-Chicken_98301_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPP_Baked-Parmesan-Chicken_98292_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPP_Baked-Parmesan-Chicken_98316_WEB_high_feature.jpg\n0108_FPP_Baked-Parmesan-Chicken_98320_WEB_high_feature.jpg', 'Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then preheat to 450 degrees. Heat a medium pot of salted water to boiling on high. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut off and discard the bottom 1/2 inch of the broccoli stem; cut the broccoli into small pieces, keeping the florets intact. Quarter and deseed the lemon. Peel and medium dice the sweet potatoes.\r\n\r\nPlace the broccoli pieces on a sheet pan. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper; toss to coat. Arrange in an even layer. Roast 16 to 18 minutes, or until browned and tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven. Evenly top with the juice of 2 lemon wedges.\r\n\r\nWhile the broccoli roasts, add the diced sweet potatoes to the pot of boiling water. Cook 14 to 16 minutes, or until tender when pierced with a fork. Turn off the heat. Drain thoroughly and return to the pot. Add the butter and a drizzle of olive oil. Using a fork, mash to your desired consistency; season with salt and pepper to taste. Cover to keep warm.\r\n\r\nWhile the sweet potatoes cook, on a large plate, combine the flour, half the cheese, and all but a pinch of the spice blend; season with salt and pepper. Pat the chicken dry with paper towels; season with salt and pepper on both sides. Working one piece at a time, thoroughly coat the seasoned chicken in the flour mixture (tapping off any excess). Transfer to a separate plate.\r\n\r\nWhile the sweet potatoes continue to cook, in a large pan (nonstick, if you have one), heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. Add the coated chicken and cook 5 to 7 minutes per side, or until golden brown and cooked through. Turn off the heat.\r\n\r\nWhile the chicken cooks, in a bowl, combine the mayonnaise, remaining spice blend, and the juice of the remaining lemon wedges; season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve the cooked chicken, roasted broccoli, and mashed sweet potatoes with the sauce on the side. Garnish the chicken with the remaining cheese. Enjoy!', 'Recipe_ParmesanCrusted_Chicken_with_Mashed_Sweet_Potatoes_Roasted_Broccoli');

